$At the close of the game, fans crowded around Browns Owner Phil Ball's box to boo, jeer, and call him abusive names. He remained seated and laughed in defiance of the mob. Plainclothesmen were rushed in to push back the growing crowd as they echoed, 'We want Jake' Fans believed that Browns' losing streak would not have happened if only Ball would come to terms with Jacobson who was holding out.
